3:
These ten times you have reproached me;
\q you are not ashamed that you have treated me harshly.
\q

10:
He has broken me down on every side, and I am gone;
\q he has plucked up my hopes like a tree.
\q

11:
He has also kindled his wrath against me;
\q he regards me as one of his adversaries.
\q

12:
His troops come on together;
\q they cast up siege mounds against me
\q and encamp around my tent.

13:
He has put my brothers far from me;
\q my acquaintances are wholly alienated from me.
\q

15:
Those who once stayed as guests in my house and my female servants regard me as a stranger;
\q I am an alien in their sight.
\q

17:
My breath is offensive to my wife;
\q I am even disgusting to those who were born from my mother's womb.
\q

18:
Even young children despise me;
\q if I rise to speak, they speak against me.
\q

20:
My bones cling to my skin and to my flesh;
\q I survive only by the skin of my teeth.
\q

25:
But as for me, I know that my Redeemer lives,
\q and that at last he will stand on the earth;
\q

27:
I will see him myself;
\q my eyes—and not someone else—will see him.
\q My kidneys fail within me
